---
title: One-Pot Cheesy Taco Turkey & Bean Soup with Scallions
description: Who doesn’t love a warming, cozy pot of soup? Break out your big spoons for this delicious one-pot, 20-minute dinner idea. This one boasts all the flavors of savory turkey and bean tacos in one light-but-satisfying bowl. It starts with ground turkey sautéed with our blend of Southwest spices, plus garlic, onion, and tomato for a deeply flavored broth. You’ll add hearty red beans, shredded Mexican cheese, a dash of hot sauce, and finish with a sprinkle of fresh scallions (and even more cheese!).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pot-cheesy-taco-turkey-bean-soup-a0eda379.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64646553c59968f5f00b128d.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-cheesy-taco-turkey-bean-soup-64646553c59968f5f00b128d
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Mexican
nutrition:
  calories: 570 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 37 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1080 mg
---

Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice
@tomato{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large #pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until turkey is lightly
browned and mostly cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in
the next step).

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Add garlic, scallion whites, and @tomato paste{1} to pot; cook, stirring, until
fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add diced tomato, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, and
@sugar{3/4%tsp} to pot with turkey mixture; stir until well combined.

Stir in half the @kidney beans{1%can} and their liquid and 1 1/2 cups water;
bring to a simmer and cook until tomato is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off
heat.

Stir in half the @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp}
as you like; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between #bowls{}; top with scallion greens and remaining
Mexican cheese blend. Serve.